#!/bin/sh

PROMPT="
Collect data that I request, below, and combine it into a morning brief formatted as html.

Print the brief to standard out in html. Use classy, compact, and simple formatting designed for easy and quick reading. 
Use black text, background color #EBEBE6, and jewel tones as accents. 
Hyperlink article titles and other information on the web that you refer to.

Respond with raw HTML only.
Do not output markdown, code fences, or explanations. Just the HTML document starting with <!DOCTYPE html>.
Do not narrate or explain what you are doing.
The first line of your output must be <!DOCTYPE html> .
The last line of your output must be </html> .
Everything in between those must be valid html.

Requested data:
- top 3 articles from https://www.canarymedia.com/, one summary per article, of 15 words or less, per article.
- top 3 articles from https://www.npr.com/, one summary, of 15 words or less, per article.
- An estimate, expressed as a percentage, and a discussion of length 60 to 80 words about the probability of severe storms over North Dakota in the next 7 days, in the area between Bismark and Dickinson. Ignore all risks not directly associated with severe storms, such as fire and wind. To make your estimate, review https://www.spc.noaa.gov/products/exper/day4-8/, https://www.spc.noaa.gov/products/outlook/day3otlk.html, https://www.spc.noaa.gov/products/outlook/day2otlk.html, https://www.spc.noaa.gov/products/outlook/day1otlk.html, https://forecast.weather.gov/showsigwx.php?warnzone=NDZ033&warncounty=NDC089&firewxzone=NDZ033&local_place1=3+Miles+ENE+Dickinson+Theodore+Roosevelt+Regional+Airport+ND&product1=Hazardous+Weather+Outlook, and https://forecast.weather.gov/showsigwx.php?warnzone=NDZ035&warncounty=NDC015&firewxzone=NDZ035&local_place1=Bismarck%20ND&product1=Hazardous+Weather+Outlook&lat=46.8083&lon=-100.7837 . Use your judgement to create the requested estimate and discussion.

If you encounter problems, try web search or other work arounds.

If you report both content from articles and information on your own activites, put the content first and the information on your activities at the very end.

This is an automated script and you should not ask questions because I will not be able to answer them.
"

/home/ubuntu/.nvm/versions/node/v24.15.0/bin/claude --allowedTools WebFetch,WebSearch -p "$PROMPT" | sed -n '/<\!DOCTYPE/,$ p'
